1
00:00:05,356 --> 00:00:07,357
As the new troupe leader,

2
00:00:07,357 --> 00:00:08,274
I’ve decided

3
00:00:08,274 --> 00:00:10,506
to focus fully on taking care of the troupe.

4
00:00:11,173 --> 00:00:12,509
And I won’t perform anymore.

5
00:00:12,842 --> 00:00:13,749
Tor Prakai

6
00:00:14,271 --> 00:00:16,314
will be our new Likay hero.

7
00:00:17,090 --> 00:00:18,023
I wanna be you.

8
00:00:18,223 --> 00:00:19,390
What’s so bad about being you?

9
00:00:19,690 --> 00:00:21,656
Try being me sometime, then you’ll know.

10
00:00:22,156 --> 00:00:24,806
What’s your name? Can I get your contact?

11
00:00:25,023 --> 00:00:25,690
Are you hitting on me?

12
00:00:25,890 --> 00:00:28,601
Now that Father’s gone,
and Jom Thian and Chan Dao are gone too,

13
00:00:28,601 --> 00:00:30,660
It made me realize how easy things used to be

14
00:00:30,660 --> 00:00:31,656
when everyone was still here.

15
00:00:32,423 --> 00:00:33,440
P’Phet, do you know

16
00:00:33,440 --> 00:00:35,256
that everyone feels lonely sometimes?

17
00:00:35,690 --> 00:00:37,556
I just want to repay you somehow.

18
00:00:37,890 --> 00:00:39,656
I want to be someone who stays by your side.

19
00:00:40,190 --> 00:00:41,124
Ploy, to me

20
00:00:41,385 --> 00:00:42,823
you’re not just a little sister.

21
00:00:45,490 --> 00:00:46,490
Have you seen Guy?

22
00:00:47,056 --> 00:00:48,116
Did you two see him?

23
00:00:54,223 --> 00:00:56,356
The eyeliner will be around here.

24
00:00:57,190 --> 00:00:58,190
And then there will be—

25
00:00:58,390 --> 00:00:59,290
Someone saying,

26
00:00:59,423 --> 00:01:00,303
“Ah, thank you very much.”

27
00:01:00,303 --> 00:01:00,803
Yes.

28
00:01:00,803 --> 00:01:02,242
“Ah, thank you very much,” and then get startled.

29
00:01:03,290 --> 00:01:04,490
The startled part goes like this.

30
00:01:31,656 --> 00:01:32,490
I love you.

31
00:01:34,456 --> 00:01:36,156
I don’t care what gender you are.

32
00:01:38,856 --> 00:01:40,090
Because my heart

33
00:01:41,890 --> 00:01:43,456
says it has to be you.

34
00:01:45,590 --> 00:01:46,490
I feel the same way.

35
00:01:48,823 --> 00:01:51,023
I don’t want to hide anymore.

36
00:02:21,190 --> 00:02:22,623
Isn’t this the sidewalk?

37
00:02:22,990 --> 00:02:25,156
The crew can go take a meal break.

38
00:02:31,656 --> 00:02:33,856
Sorry, Nine. The shoot ran late today.

39
00:02:34,023 --> 00:02:34,953
No problem,

40
00:02:34,953 --> 00:02:37,690
P’. So what are we eating today? I’m starving.

41
00:02:37,873 --> 00:02:42,739
Today? Stir-fried vegetables with a ghost of chicken,
and fried rice.

42
00:02:44,556 --> 00:02:46,063
Uh, then I think

43
00:02:46,324 --> 00:02:47,802
I’ll go find something to eat outside.

44
00:02:48,019 --> 00:02:50,056
Please tell the crew I’ll be back.

45
00:02:50,223 --> 00:02:51,023
You really going with that?

46
00:02:51,290 --> 00:02:51,823
Yes.

47
00:02:51,823 --> 00:02:52,323
Oh.

48
00:02:53,539 --> 00:02:54,339
Yeah.

49
00:02:54,552 --> 00:02:55,352
Yeah.

50
00:02:56,056 --> 00:02:56,823
Yeah.

51
00:02:56,823 --> 00:02:57,323
Mm.

52
00:02:57,323 --> 00:02:57,823
Yeah.

53
00:03:08,192 --> 00:03:09,023
I’m sorry.

54
00:03:09,023 --> 00:03:10,165
Can you stand up?

55
00:03:11,037 --> 00:03:11,726
I’m sorry.

56
00:03:17,966 --> 00:03:18,631
My wallet.

57
00:03:20,428 --> 00:03:21,047
Hey, you.

58
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,581
Give me back my wallet right now.

59
00:03:23,890 --> 00:03:24,690
Me?

60
00:03:26,090 --> 00:03:27,023
If you don’t return it,

61
00:03:29,290 --> 00:03:30,423
I’m calling the police.

62
00:03:30,590 --> 00:03:31,623
I took your photo too.

63
00:03:31,623 --> 00:03:32,123
Hey, delete it.

64
00:03:32,742 --> 00:03:33,520
Give it back first.

65
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:34,020
Hey, delete it.

66
00:03:34,856 --> 00:03:35,933
Then give it back.

67
00:03:35,933 --> 00:03:36,907
I said delete it.

68
00:03:36,907 --> 00:03:37,871
Then give it back first.

69
00:03:38,109 --> 00:03:39,054
I said delete it.

70
00:03:39,054 --> 00:03:40,504
Then give it back first, you thief.

71
00:03:40,504 --> 00:03:41,356
I said delete it!

72
00:03:41,373 --> 00:03:41,911
I said delete it!

73
00:03:41,911 --> 00:03:43,461
Give it back, you thief!

74
00:04:01,890 --> 00:04:03,058
Hey, you.

75
00:04:03,344 --> 00:04:06,222
Someone helped you and you can’t even say thank you.

76
00:04:06,555 --> 00:04:09,042
Why should I thank a thief?

77
00:04:09,890 --> 00:04:10,690
Hey.

78
00:04:13,490 --> 00:04:15,056
You forgot your wallet at the shop.

79
00:04:15,390 --> 00:04:15,890
Wow.

80
00:04:16,101 --> 00:04:17,210
I’ve been looking for you everywhere.

81
00:04:20,890 --> 00:04:21,990
Here, it’s yours.

82
00:04:23,090 --> 00:04:23,956
Thank you very much.

83
00:04:24,490 --> 00:04:25,456
I’ll get going now.

84
00:04:26,390 --> 00:04:27,390
Uh, sir.

85
00:04:32,490 --> 00:04:33,290
Here.

86
00:04:33,423 --> 00:04:34,623
Please take this as a small token.

87
00:04:35,590 --> 00:04:36,390
Thank you.

88
00:04:36,590 --> 00:04:37,390
Thank you.

89
00:04:40,956 --> 00:04:42,990
So who’s the thief now?

90
00:04:44,490 --> 00:04:46,456
Alright, alright.

91
00:04:47,656 --> 00:04:48,556
Fine, I’m sorry.

92
00:04:49,190 --> 00:04:50,590
What, like you’ve never made a mistake?

93
00:04:51,656 --> 00:04:52,590
When you kissed me,

94
00:04:52,856 --> 00:04:53,893
I didn’t even make a big deal out of it.

95
00:04:54,645 --> 00:04:55,623
Who kissed you?

96
00:04:57,015 --> 00:04:58,423
Saying that makes me look bad, you know.

97
00:04:58,590 --> 00:04:59,556
I’m the one who’s losing here.

98
00:05:00,356 --> 00:05:01,390
I’m the one who got kissed.

99
00:05:01,790 --> 00:05:02,456
Hey.

100
00:05:02,456 --> 00:05:04,790
Did you hit your head so hard your brain fell out?

101
00:05:05,090 --> 00:05:05,890
Huh?

102
00:05:07,656 --> 00:05:08,727
But it’s okay.

103
00:05:09,394 --> 00:05:10,394
I forgive you.

104
00:05:12,394 --> 00:05:13,057
Let’s call it even.

105
00:07:05,290 --> 00:07:06,090
Hey.

106
00:07:06,823 --> 00:07:07,656
No need to stress.

107
00:07:07,890 --> 00:07:09,156
Nephew Phet, no need to stress.

108
00:07:09,756 --> 00:07:10,556
We’re like family here.

109
00:07:10,990 --> 00:07:11,690
Right?

110
00:07:11,690 --> 00:07:12,490
Mm.

111
00:07:13,290 --> 00:07:15,223
If you have something to say, just say it.

112
00:07:15,290 --> 00:07:17,156
So we don’t waste time.

113
00:07:18,356 --> 00:07:19,423
Don’t say it like that.

114
00:07:19,756 --> 00:07:20,556
Nephew Phet.

115
00:07:21,604 --> 00:07:23,015
The reason I came here

116
00:07:23,491 --> 00:07:24,491
is nothing much.

117
00:07:25,842 --> 00:07:27,707
It’s about our loan contract.

118
00:07:28,272 --> 00:07:30,061
I’m here about our contract,

119
00:07:31,257 --> 00:07:31,757
right?

120
00:07:35,866 --> 00:07:37,590
But I’ve already signed the contract.

121
00:07:38,023 --> 00:07:38,551
And

122
00:07:38,837 --> 00:07:40,751
I’ve already given you the first payment.

123
00:07:40,751 --> 00:07:41,251
Mm.

124
00:07:41,856 --> 00:07:43,756
So what else do you want?

125
00:07:44,290 --> 00:07:46,590
But if you want the second payment

126
00:07:46,790 --> 00:07:47,590
Mm.

127
00:07:48,023 --> 00:07:49,456
Right now I don’t have it.

128
00:07:49,456 --> 00:07:49,956
Mm.

129
00:07:50,790 --> 00:07:52,170
You’ll have to wait.

130
00:07:52,170 --> 00:07:53,656
It’s not due yet anyway.

131
00:07:54,290 --> 00:07:56,456
Right now I’m trying to find work.

132
00:07:59,656 --> 00:08:00,656
Kam Phet.

133
00:08:00,856 --> 00:08:01,690
Kam Ploy.

134
00:08:04,023 --> 00:08:04,823
Go.

135
00:08:11,423 --> 00:08:12,590
Go get it.

136
00:08:13,390 --> 00:08:14,456
Did they forget something?

137
00:08:15,356 --> 00:08:16,521
Or are they getting a gun?

138
00:08:16,695 --> 00:08:17,330
Huh?

139
00:08:18,356 --> 00:08:19,223
Come on then.

140
00:08:19,356 --> 00:08:21,590
Hey, calm down. Wait.

141
00:08:23,223 --> 00:08:24,390
You’ll wreck the house.

142
00:08:24,856 --> 00:08:26,056
Good thing we stopped him.

143
00:08:42,556 --> 00:08:44,213
See? Nothing happened.

144
00:08:50,056 --> 00:08:50,873
Boss,

145
00:08:51,111 --> 00:08:52,894
I’m a man of my word.

146
00:08:53,256 --> 00:08:54,056
Right.

147
00:08:54,356 --> 00:08:55,988
Since Nephew Phet

148
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:58,023
already paid the first installment,

149
00:08:58,356 --> 00:08:59,456
I’ll return this.

150
00:08:59,890 --> 00:09:00,690
How about that?

151
00:09:04,190 --> 00:09:07,156
But next time

152
00:09:08,590 --> 00:09:10,023
if you don’t pay on time,

153
00:09:10,556 --> 00:09:12,356
I can’t promise anything.

154
00:09:12,423 --> 00:09:15,309
about what I’ll do to you, Nephew Phet.

155
00:09:21,690 --> 00:09:22,490
Hey.

156
00:09:23,056 --> 00:09:23,856
Put it down.

157
00:09:24,223 --> 00:09:25,490
Yeah, carefully.

158
00:09:26,590 --> 00:09:27,656
Put it on the table.

159
00:09:27,790 --> 00:09:28,823
On the table.

160
00:09:30,056 --> 00:09:31,790
Careful.

161
00:09:32,490 --> 00:09:33,656
That’s valuable.

162
00:09:33,956 --> 00:09:34,990
Alright.

163
00:09:35,856 --> 00:09:36,790
If everything’s settled,

164
00:09:38,556 --> 00:09:40,299
I’ll take my leave

165
00:09:41,728 --> 00:09:45,703
now.

166
00:09:46,179 --> 00:09:47,814
Let’s go.

167
00:10:02,790 --> 00:10:03,734
Whoa.

168
00:10:04,067 --> 00:10:07,423
That scene just now made my heart drop.

169
00:10:07,423 --> 00:10:08,590
Mine dropped right here.

170
00:10:09,623 --> 00:10:11,190
Mine dropped all the way down here.

171
00:10:13,256 --> 00:10:14,047
P’Phet.

172
00:10:15,090 --> 00:10:16,014
Don’t worry, P’.

173
00:10:16,633 --> 00:10:18,993
As long as Pleng is still in this troupe,

174
00:10:19,469 --> 00:10:20,936
no one can bully us.

175
00:10:21,698 --> 00:10:22,511
Trust me.

176
00:10:24,110 --> 00:10:24,610
Bang.

177
00:10:24,610 --> 00:10:25,115
Hey!

178
00:10:27,953 --> 00:10:28,748
What are you doing?

179
00:10:30,681 --> 00:10:31,774
You’ll wreck the house.

180
00:10:43,790 --> 00:10:44,990
You okay, P’Phet?

181
00:10:46,490 --> 00:10:47,290
Of course.

182
00:10:48,390 --> 00:10:49,856
We made it through this month.

183
00:10:50,390 --> 00:10:51,990
We’ll make it through next month too.

184
00:10:53,590 --> 00:10:54,255
Yeah, you’re right.

185
00:10:54,874 --> 00:10:56,832
Even if a hundred problems come our way,

186
00:10:57,594 --> 00:10:58,659
we’ll face them together.

187
00:11:01,135 --> 00:11:01,690
I…

188
00:11:02,820 --> 00:11:04,556
I’m always on Team Petchprakai.

189
00:11:08,823 --> 00:11:09,890
Thanks, Ploy.

190
00:11:21,623 --> 00:11:23,974
By the way,

191
00:11:25,090 --> 00:11:26,163
Have you seen Guy?

192
00:11:28,978 --> 00:11:29,632
No.

193
00:11:43,756 --> 00:11:44,583
Boss.

194
00:11:44,583 --> 00:11:47,023
Spicy stir-fried basil with crispy pork
and a fried egg, please.

195
00:11:47,090 --> 00:11:48,990
Sure, go sit inside first.

196
00:11:49,356 --> 00:11:50,356
I’ll make it for you.

197
00:11:50,556 --> 00:11:51,056
Alright.

198
00:12:13,490 --> 00:12:14,785
How’d it go today?

199
00:12:15,499 --> 00:12:17,658
I saw you taking photos for that

200
00:12:17,658 --> 00:12:18,158
What was that called?

201
00:12:18,801 --> 00:12:19,776
that flimflam thing.

202
00:12:19,776 --> 00:12:21,110
Yeah.

203
00:12:21,586 --> 00:12:22,852
Profile picture.

204
00:12:23,290 --> 00:12:24,456
Yeah, profile picture.

205
00:12:25,556 --> 00:12:27,256
So how did it go, man?

206
00:12:27,490 --> 00:12:29,890
Pretty good. They said my left side looks better.

207
00:12:30,956 --> 00:12:31,990
You think that’s true?

208
00:12:34,256 --> 00:12:35,156
Yeah, you look good.

209
00:12:37,956 --> 00:12:39,636
So did you become a star yet?

210
00:12:39,636 --> 00:12:40,356
Man.

211
00:12:40,823 --> 00:12:42,656
They just sent my photos to the first casting round.

212
00:12:43,290 --> 00:12:44,256
If the producer likes them,

213
00:12:44,490 --> 00:12:46,056
they’ll call me back for another casting.

214
00:12:47,890 --> 00:12:49,656
One crispy pork basil with fried egg, boss.

215
00:12:49,823 --> 00:12:50,581
Sure.

216
00:12:51,343 --> 00:12:52,788
But the tables are full right now.

217
00:12:53,121 --> 00:12:55,290
Hey handsome, could you sit over there?

218
00:12:55,823 --> 00:12:56,690
He’s here alone.

219
00:12:56,956 --> 00:12:58,052
Order the same thing and

220
00:12:58,052 --> 00:12:59,490
I’ll cook them together.

221
00:12:59,823 --> 00:13:00,590
Sure, boss.

222
00:13:00,590 --> 00:13:01,790
Go sit and wait. I’ll cook it for you.

223
00:13:01,956 --> 00:13:03,356
Man, this is exciting.

224
00:13:03,556 --> 00:13:05,290
We’re about to have a celebrity friend.

225
00:13:06,690 --> 00:13:07,490
What?

226
00:13:09,256 --> 00:13:10,056
Yeah.

227
00:13:14,256 --> 00:13:14,793
Hey.

228
00:13:16,793 --> 00:13:17,757
I’ll hang up now.

229
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:19,713
I just ran into that thief.

230
00:13:23,156 --> 00:13:25,090
You’re still calling me a thief?

231
00:13:25,223 --> 00:13:26,023
Why should I stop?

232
00:13:26,390 --> 00:13:27,987
Following me like this makes it even clearer.

233
00:13:27,987 --> 00:13:28,487
Following you?

234
00:13:28,756 --> 00:13:29,556
Who’s following you?

235
00:13:30,823 --> 00:13:31,823
You’re pretty full of yourself, huh?

236
00:13:32,623 --> 00:13:34,390
Anyone can eat here.

237
00:13:35,656 --> 00:13:37,948
I was here first. If you’re not leaving,

238
00:13:38,329 --> 00:13:39,456
then get away from my table.

239
00:13:39,656 --> 00:13:40,855
Wow, I didn’t know

240
00:13:41,289 --> 00:13:43,356
buying food here came with a table.

241
00:13:46,623 --> 00:13:47,756
You hairy guy.

242
00:13:48,823 --> 00:13:49,623
Hairy guy?

243
00:13:53,623 --> 00:13:55,076
What the hell is “hairy guy”?

244
00:13:55,076 --> 00:13:55,690
Just look at you.

245
00:13:58,690 --> 00:14:00,756
Checking your stuff again, thief?

246
00:14:00,823 --> 00:14:01,670
What thief?

247
00:14:01,670 --> 00:14:02,356
You’re hairy.

248
00:14:02,595 --> 00:14:03,095
Thief.

249
00:14:03,656 --> 00:14:04,210
Looks like you’re really hairy down there.

250
00:14:04,210 --> 00:14:04,969
You’re the thief.

251
00:14:05,223 --> 00:14:06,556
Then why are you snooping around?

252
00:14:06,656 --> 00:14:07,590
Please don’t argue.

253
00:14:07,690 --> 00:14:08,490
Here.

254
00:14:08,890 --> 00:14:10,719
You’re both eating the same crispy pork basil.

255
00:14:11,490 --> 00:14:12,775
Better get along.

256
00:14:12,775 --> 00:14:13,556
Here.

257
00:14:14,890 --> 00:14:15,823
Chili fish sauce.

258
00:14:23,223 --> 00:14:23,723
Let go.

259
00:14:23,723 --> 00:14:24,223
You let go!

260
00:14:24,556 --> 00:14:25,971
What’s your problem, hairy guy?

261
00:14:25,971 --> 00:14:26,471
That’s mine.

262
00:14:26,656 --> 00:14:27,713
I grabbed it first.
(Tor Prakai) I was here first.

263
00:14:28,072 --> 00:14:28,778
(Nine) I grabbed it first.

264
00:14:28,778 --> 00:14:29,895
So I should get it first, right?

265
00:14:30,156 --> 00:14:30,656
You hairy guy!

266
00:14:30,890 --> 00:14:31,390
Let go.

267
00:14:31,390 --> 00:14:32,142
You thief!

268
00:14:32,142 --> 00:14:33,243
You’re even stealing the fish sauce now?

269
00:14:33,690 --> 00:14:34,490
I grabbed it first.

270
00:14:34,490 --> 00:14:34,990
Mine.

271
00:14:35,390 --> 00:14:36,023
I grabbed it first.

272
00:14:36,023 --> 00:14:36,823
I was here first too.

273
00:14:36,823 --> 00:14:37,156
I grabbed it first.

274
00:14:37,156 --> 00:14:38,356
Are you crazy?

275
00:14:38,490 --> 00:14:39,246
You are.

276
00:14:39,246 --> 00:14:39,746
Wow.

277
00:14:39,956 --> 00:14:40,756
I said let go.

278
00:14:52,623 --> 00:14:53,950
Hello, Ma'am

279
00:14:55,090 --> 00:14:57,355
Yes, this is Phet Thae,

280
00:14:57,833 --> 00:14:59,818
son of Father Thong Pleaw

281
00:15:00,390 --> 00:15:02,143
from the Petchprakai Likay Troupe.

282
00:15:03,656 --> 00:15:04,196
Yes

283
00:15:04,196 --> 00:15:05,833
I’m calling to let you know

284
00:15:05,833 --> 00:15:07,113
that I’m now

285
00:15:07,896 --> 00:15:09,165
the new troupe leader.

286
00:15:09,643 --> 00:15:11,227
If you’re organizing

287
00:15:11,662 --> 00:15:13,019
any events,

288
00:15:13,019 --> 00:15:14,910
you can contact this number.

289
00:15:16,456 --> 00:15:18,256
Oh, you’re having a ceremony?

290
00:15:21,056 --> 00:15:23,896
But you already hired another troupe?

291
00:15:26,134 --> 00:15:27,138
No, that’s alright.

292
00:15:27,519 --> 00:15:28,156
Yes.

293
00:15:28,728 --> 00:15:29,970
But next time

294
00:15:29,970 --> 00:15:31,707
if you organize an event,

295
00:15:32,469 --> 00:15:34,222
please keep the Petchprakai troupe in mind.

296
00:15:35,794 --> 00:15:36,371
Yes.

297
00:15:37,133 --> 00:15:37,790
Goodbye.

298
00:15:53,690 --> 00:15:55,456
Cold bael juice is here.

299
00:16:01,890 --> 00:16:02,752
P’Phet.

300
00:16:04,657 --> 00:16:06,162
What are you eating?

301
00:16:06,162 --> 00:16:09,590
There’s no nutrition in that. You’ll collapse.

302
00:16:10,023 --> 00:16:10,658
Oh.

303
00:16:11,372 --> 00:16:12,387
It’s just quick and easy.

304
00:16:13,483 --> 00:16:14,765
Just enough to fill my stomach

305
00:16:15,289 --> 00:16:17,494
so I can keep working right away.

306
00:16:18,690 --> 00:16:19,956
Want me to help?

307
00:16:22,656 --> 00:16:23,683
No, Ploy.

308
00:16:23,683 --> 00:16:26,763
I’d rather call the event hosts myself.

309
00:16:27,192 --> 00:16:29,651
So I can introduce myself as the new troupe leader.

310
00:16:30,318 --> 00:16:33,929
That way they’ll know we care.

311
00:16:34,501 --> 00:16:37,039
You just focus on your practice.

312
00:16:40,590 --> 00:16:42,656
I’m already doing my best.

313
00:16:54,156 --> 00:16:55,506
Hello.

314
00:16:57,173 --> 00:16:58,277
This is Phet Thae speaking.

315
00:16:58,610 --> 00:17:00,175
Son of Father Thongplao.

316
00:17:02,256 --> 00:17:03,293
Yes,

317
00:17:03,293 --> 00:17:04,966
I’m currently the new troupe leader.

318
00:17:05,776 --> 00:17:07,704
Are you planning…

319
00:17:10,890 --> 00:17:11,690
Pleng.

320
00:17:12,023 --> 00:17:14,056
Help me find a fish stall.

321
00:17:14,390 --> 00:17:15,423
Is it around here?

322
00:17:16,556 --> 00:17:18,356
Just keep walking. We’ll find one ahead.

323
00:17:18,423 --> 00:17:19,790
You sure you’re not getting us lost?

324
00:17:19,956 --> 00:17:20,790
We’re already by the canal.

325
00:17:21,156 --> 00:17:21,956
The fish stall should be around here.

326
00:17:22,190 --> 00:17:23,056
I said help look for it.

327
00:17:23,190 --> 00:17:23,756
Wait, wait.

328
00:17:23,756 --> 00:17:25,090
(Ploy Ying) Stop playing your game first.
(Pleng Chai) I was ranking up.

329
00:17:25,090 --> 00:17:25,590
Give it here.

330
00:17:25,590 --> 00:17:26,156
Wait, I’ll help in a second.

331
00:17:26,156 --> 00:17:27,123
(Ploy Ying) No.
(Pleng Chai) Just a second.

332
00:17:27,123 --> 00:17:27,656
Stop.

333
00:17:29,623 --> 00:17:30,360
Hey.

334
00:17:30,360 --> 00:17:31,756
Hey, you.

335
00:17:31,990 --> 00:17:32,890
What, scared of ghosts?

336
00:17:33,256 --> 00:17:35,090
Of course not. Who’s scared?

337
00:17:36,623 --> 00:17:38,535
Then I could say

338
00:17:39,440 --> 00:17:40,990
there’s a kid sitting on your shoulder right now.

339
00:17:44,890 --> 00:17:47,223
Take that back right now.

340
00:17:47,290 --> 00:17:48,690
Okay, sorry, sorry.

341
00:17:53,490 --> 00:17:54,290
You’re easy to scare.

342
00:17:54,390 --> 00:17:56,990
Why’d you throw it this way?

343
00:17:57,156 --> 00:17:58,556
You’re kinda funny.

344
00:18:00,990 --> 00:18:02,290
So you’re scared of ghosts?

345
00:18:02,990 --> 00:18:03,790
No way.

346
00:18:04,223 --> 00:18:04,956
I’m not scared.

347
00:18:04,956 --> 00:18:05,756
Mm.

348
00:18:05,990 --> 00:18:07,556
You jumped like a fish just now.

349
00:18:07,756 --> 00:18:08,556
I was just startled.

350
00:18:09,823 --> 00:18:10,623
Wait.

351
00:18:10,656 --> 00:18:12,490
Are you the Likay heroine, Matthri?

352
00:18:12,690 --> 00:18:13,690
From the Petchprakai troupe?

353
00:18:15,456 --> 00:18:16,256
Yes.

354
00:18:17,690 --> 00:18:19,156
You’re so cute in person.

355
00:18:21,223 --> 00:18:22,023
Thank you.

356
00:18:22,590 --> 00:18:23,183
In person?

357
00:18:23,707 --> 00:18:25,889
So that dancer the other day was fake then.

358
00:18:26,856 --> 00:18:27,656
Oh.

359
00:18:27,756 --> 00:18:28,756
Pleng.

360
00:18:32,156 --> 00:18:34,668
Thank you. Come watch Likay again sometime.

361
00:18:34,668 --> 00:18:37,507
Sure, I definitely will. I love it.

362
00:18:37,507 --> 00:18:39,069
I was there that day and took

363
00:18:39,069 --> 00:18:41,623
lots of photos of you. Want to see them?

364
00:18:45,756 --> 00:18:47,056
Sure, thank you.

365
00:18:47,390 --> 00:18:49,356
Do you want them? I can drop them to you.

366
00:18:49,756 --> 00:18:50,990
Drop them to me?

367
00:18:51,156 --> 00:18:52,041
AirDrop.

368
00:18:52,476 --> 00:18:53,823
Just turn on AirDrop on your phone.

369
00:18:53,956 --> 00:18:54,756
Okay.

370
00:18:55,056 --> 00:18:55,856
Can you do it?

371
00:18:56,656 --> 00:18:57,823
What’s your phone name?

372
00:18:58,356 --> 00:18:59,590
Ploy Ying.

373
00:19:00,290 --> 00:19:02,223
Your name is Ploy Ying?

374
00:19:03,199 --> 00:19:03,990
Yes

375
00:19:03,990 --> 00:19:04,790
That’s a cute name.

376
00:19:05,023 --> 00:19:05,823
Ploy Ying.

377
00:19:06,790 --> 00:19:08,190
My name is Lynchee.

378
00:19:08,590 --> 00:19:09,496
Lynchee.

379
00:19:09,496 --> 00:19:09,996
Yes.

380
00:19:11,556 --> 00:19:12,823
Did you get them?

381
00:19:13,290 --> 00:19:14,090
Got it.

382
00:19:14,423 --> 00:19:15,223
Wow.

383
00:19:15,290 --> 00:19:16,656
These photos are really beautiful.

384
00:19:17,090 --> 00:19:17,890
Thank you.

385
00:19:17,890 --> 00:19:18,690
See?

386
00:19:18,790 --> 00:19:19,590
Thank you.

387
00:19:20,423 --> 00:19:21,490
Of course they’re beautiful.

388
00:19:22,556 --> 00:19:24,264
I adjusted the camera that day.

389
00:19:24,836 --> 00:19:25,423
Right?

390
00:19:26,490 --> 00:19:26,990
Yep.

391
00:19:27,847 --> 00:19:28,701
You’re determined to be one, huh?

392
00:19:28,987 --> 00:19:30,456
The most talented guy in the world.

393
00:19:30,823 --> 00:19:32,056
Of course he is.

394
00:19:32,390 --> 00:19:33,282
Good at everything.

395
00:19:33,282 --> 00:19:33,782
Why?

396
00:19:33,782 --> 00:19:34,392
He speaks well too.

397
00:19:34,392 --> 00:19:36,356
(Pleng Chai) I’m good at a lot of things.
(Ploy Ying) And you’re good at arguing, too.

398
00:19:36,656 --> 00:19:37,890
Ploy Ying.

399
00:19:38,456 --> 00:19:39,256
Yes?

400
00:19:40,056 --> 00:19:41,756
Would you be interested in becoming an actress?

401
00:19:42,356 --> 00:19:43,117
(Ploy Ying) Huh?
(Pleng Chai) Huh?

402
00:19:47,013 --> 00:19:47,813
An actress.

403
00:20:14,290 --> 00:20:15,090
Where were you?

404
00:20:25,656 --> 00:20:26,189
Well…

405
00:20:27,094 --> 00:20:29,456
To Bangkok.

406
00:20:30,075 --> 00:20:31,232
To buy fabric for costumes.

407
00:20:32,990 --> 00:20:34,168
That early in the morning?

408
00:20:35,090 --> 00:20:36,250
Doesn’t that shop open in the afternoon?

409
00:20:38,090 --> 00:20:38,890
Well…

410
00:20:40,390 --> 00:20:41,623
I bought other things too.

411
00:20:50,290 --> 00:20:51,090
Two things.

412
00:20:54,656 --> 00:20:55,456
Guy.

413
00:21:10,023 --> 00:21:11,090
Thank you so much.

414
00:21:12,490 --> 00:21:14,290
For doing this for Petchprakai.

415
00:21:15,623 --> 00:21:18,790
I didn’t think you’d take this so seriously.

416
00:21:23,623 --> 00:21:25,039
What our future will look like

417
00:21:26,420 --> 00:21:27,813
also depends on you, Guy.

418
00:21:31,656 --> 00:21:33,256
You bought a lot. Is it heavy?

419
00:21:33,856 --> 00:21:35,890
No, no. It’s fine. It’s not that much.

420
00:21:37,890 --> 00:21:38,418
Oh.

421
00:21:38,704 --> 00:21:40,709
Where did you two go?

422
00:21:41,356 --> 00:21:41,856
Oh.

423
00:21:42,189 --> 00:21:43,172
We went to the market.

424
00:21:43,553 --> 00:21:45,437
Auntie Da was selling bua loy today,

425
00:21:45,437 --> 00:21:46,913
so I took Pleng to get some.

426
00:21:47,423 --> 00:21:48,223
Right, Pleng?

427
00:21:48,456 --> 00:21:51,456
Yeah, Auntie Da’s bua loy was really good today.

428
00:21:51,756 --> 00:21:52,790
Oh, Auntie Da’s stall.

429
00:21:53,256 --> 00:21:53,876
Yeah.

430
00:21:53,876 --> 00:21:56,319
She rarely opens, so I took him there.

431
00:21:56,319 --> 00:21:57,286
After eating, my throat—

432
00:21:58,023 --> 00:21:59,489
—went hoarse. My throat’s dry.

433
00:21:59,489 --> 00:22:00,298
Really dry.

434
00:22:00,472 --> 00:22:01,020
My throat’s dry.

435
00:22:01,194 --> 00:22:01,694
It burns.

436
00:22:01,694 --> 00:22:02,336
It was too sweet.

437
00:22:02,336 --> 00:22:04,205
Super sweet.

438
00:22:04,205 --> 00:22:05,436
I’ll go drink some water first.

439
00:22:05,784 --> 00:22:07,476
My throat’s hoarse. I’m getting water.

440
00:22:07,476 --> 00:22:08,916
Going to get water.

441
00:22:17,623 --> 00:22:19,113
Go put the stuff away, Guy.

442
00:22:19,113 --> 00:22:20,023
Okay.

443
00:22:20,256 --> 00:22:21,056
I can help.

444
00:22:21,423 --> 00:22:22,256
It’s fine.

445
00:22:23,456 --> 00:22:24,256
I can do it.

446
00:22:24,790 --> 00:22:26,056
It’s light.

447
00:22:31,756 --> 00:22:32,556
Ow.

448
00:22:32,623 --> 00:22:33,423
Ow.

449
00:22:33,490 --> 00:22:34,090
What’s this?

450
00:22:34,090 --> 00:22:35,990
Come help cook.

451
00:22:35,990 --> 00:22:36,490
Ow.

452
00:22:37,423 --> 00:22:38,223
What’s this?

453
00:22:39,056 --> 00:22:39,856
What?

454
00:22:39,990 --> 00:22:40,790
Don’t tell me—

455
00:22:42,390 --> 00:22:43,156
You’re cooking yourself?

456
00:22:43,156 --> 00:22:44,475
Yeah.

457
00:22:44,475 --> 00:22:47,658
If you want everyone to eat something good and healthy,

458
00:22:47,991 --> 00:22:49,389
you’ve got to cook it yourself.

459
00:22:50,023 --> 00:22:51,981
If you want to eat, come help cook.

460
00:22:52,267 --> 00:22:54,142
You boil the eggs. I’ll handle this.

461
00:22:54,623 --> 00:22:57,990
Try trusting me for once.

462
00:22:58,423 --> 00:22:59,223
Yeah.

463
00:22:59,256 --> 00:23:00,356
You can do it.

464
00:23:00,590 --> 00:23:01,623
Okay, okay.

465
00:23:01,756 --> 00:23:03,256
Alright, I’ll start here.

466
00:23:05,223 --> 00:23:06,356
Watch my skills.

467
00:23:10,256 --> 00:23:11,056
Hey.

468
00:23:11,856 --> 00:23:12,656
It’s stuck.

469
00:23:13,390 --> 00:23:14,190
Okay, okay.

470
00:23:14,223 --> 00:23:15,023
How’s that?

471
00:23:15,423 --> 00:23:15,923
Here.

472
00:23:15,923 --> 00:23:16,423
Ploy.

473
00:23:17,256 --> 00:23:18,058
Handle that.

474
00:23:18,058 --> 00:23:20,090
I’ll make the stir-fried morning glory.

475
00:23:22,423 --> 00:23:23,456
This one’s edible.

476
00:23:23,590 --> 00:23:24,656
Can we eat this?

477
00:23:24,823 --> 00:23:25,623
Yes.

478
00:23:25,956 --> 00:23:28,356
Just boil the eggs.

479
00:23:29,223 --> 00:23:30,590
Let me help.

480
00:23:31,652 --> 00:23:32,521
Is the charcoal fire too strong?

481
00:23:32,521 --> 00:23:33,390
What are you doing?

482
00:23:33,390 --> 00:23:34,290
What’s left?

483
00:23:34,423 --> 00:23:35,256
Tom yum?

484
00:23:42,297 --> 00:23:45,013
(Pleng Chai) Pass it here, hurry!
(Ploy Ying) Where do I put it? Where should I take it?

485
00:23:46,107 --> 00:23:47,281
(Ploy Ying) This one, this one!
(Chae) Delicious.

486
00:23:49,714 --> 00:23:51,149
Just leave this like this.

487
00:23:55,885 --> 00:23:57,146
Smells so good.

488
00:24:03,901 --> 00:24:05,901
(Phet Tae) This one’s ready.
(Ploy Ying) All set.

489
00:24:06,414 --> 00:24:07,545
Can we eat it yet?

490
00:24:08,001 --> 00:24:09,567
(Pleng Chai) Freshly cooked.
(Chae) Yep, go ahead!

491
00:24:14,515 --> 00:24:16,124
What are you guys doing?

492
00:24:35,834 --> 00:24:37,008
(Ploy Ying) It’s delicious.
(Pleng Chai) How is it?

493
00:24:37,552 --> 00:24:38,509
It’s good.

494
00:24:40,924 --> 00:24:42,695
So good.

495
00:25:14,556 --> 00:25:16,256
Alright, let’s eat.

496
00:25:16,656 --> 00:25:17,690
Eat up.

497
00:25:18,623 --> 00:25:19,423
Looks tasty.

498
00:25:20,023 --> 00:25:21,090
Which one’s good?

499
00:25:22,590 --> 00:25:23,556
I can’t choose.

500
00:25:34,190 --> 00:25:35,156
Not good?

501
00:25:38,423 --> 00:25:40,983
Wee-woo, wee-woo.

502
00:25:40,983 --> 00:25:45,650
An ambulance.

503
00:25:47,079 --> 00:25:48,228
So delicious.

504
00:25:48,800 --> 00:25:49,971
That’s intense.

505
00:25:50,924 --> 00:25:52,625
Oh man.

506
00:25:52,625 --> 00:25:53,482
Guy.

507
00:25:57,390 --> 00:25:58,556
What made you do this?

508
00:25:58,823 --> 00:25:59,823
Cooking yourself?

509
00:26:00,190 --> 00:26:01,490
I saw you were tired.

510
00:26:02,390 --> 00:26:03,990
So I wanted to do something for you.

511
00:26:04,190 --> 00:26:05,890
Now P’Phet’s even more tired.

512
00:26:06,190 --> 00:26:07,456
Since he had to help cook anyway.

513
00:26:08,890 --> 00:26:10,760
Not really. P’Phet’s kind.

514
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:11,260
No.

515
00:26:11,490 --> 00:26:12,623
P’Phet’s afraid we’ll start a fire.

516
00:26:13,690 --> 00:26:15,640
Ping, Pong, Chae

517
00:26:15,640 --> 00:26:17,756
—just eat already.

518
00:26:19,590 --> 00:26:20,390
Eat.

519
00:26:20,556 --> 00:26:21,556
Eat, eat.

520
00:26:27,156 --> 00:26:28,474
Eat a lot.

521
00:26:28,917 --> 00:26:29,417
What?

522
00:26:29,417 --> 00:26:30,556
There’s so much food today.

523
00:26:31,256 --> 00:26:32,056
Hey.

524
00:26:33,390 --> 00:26:34,456
Everyone, look.

525
00:26:37,223 --> 00:26:39,380
This is trending right now.

526
00:26:39,380 --> 00:26:40,945
Yesterday a famous actress

527
00:26:40,945 --> 00:26:42,995
hired a Likay troupe to perform at her wedding.

528
00:26:43,386 --> 00:26:45,330
It drew gasps from all the guests.

529
00:26:45,330 --> 00:26:46,956
It amazed the guests and went viral.

530
00:26:48,023 --> 00:26:48,523
Wow.

531
00:26:49,552 --> 00:26:52,572
P’Jomthian said their schedule is full until next year.

532
00:26:53,790 --> 00:26:55,990
So this is how great it is to be on TV.

533
00:26:57,156 --> 00:26:57,656
Yeah.

534
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:58,964
But hey,

535
00:26:58,964 --> 00:27:00,623
someone from our troupe might be on TV soon.

536
00:27:01,456 --> 00:27:02,256
Really?

537
00:27:03,256 --> 00:27:04,056
Really?

538
00:27:04,190 --> 00:27:04,990
Seriously?

539
00:27:05,990 --> 00:27:06,790
Who?

540
00:27:07,823 --> 00:27:08,602
Right here.

541
00:27:08,602 --> 00:27:09,609
It’s P’Ploy.

542
00:27:09,609 --> 00:27:11,456
She was just invited to audition as a series heroine.

543
00:27:11,656 --> 00:27:12,456
Really?

544
00:27:13,790 --> 00:27:14,702
Oh, come on.

545
00:27:15,090 --> 00:27:16,679
Why would you believe Pleng?

546
00:27:17,632 --> 00:27:19,432
I happened to meet Lynchee.

547
00:27:19,670 --> 00:27:21,406
Headman Mai’s daughter.

548
00:27:21,739 --> 00:27:23,269
She studies communications.

549
00:27:23,602 --> 00:27:25,597
She just invited me.

550
00:27:25,597 --> 00:27:26,844
It’s nothing.

551
00:27:27,023 --> 00:27:28,890
You should go. You might become famous.

552
00:27:29,356 --> 00:27:31,223
Our Likay troupe would get tons of work.

553
00:27:32,156 --> 00:27:33,356
Then should we go now?

554
00:27:33,690 --> 00:27:36,156
At least we might get one job next week.

555
00:27:49,823 --> 00:27:52,090
Hello, Petchprakai Likay Troupe speaking.

556
00:27:54,156 --> 00:27:55,090
The troupe leader?

557
00:27:55,456 --> 00:27:56,490
One moment please.

558
00:28:00,990 --> 00:28:01,790
Hello.

559
00:28:03,790 --> 00:28:05,511
Yes, we’re still available.

560
00:28:07,511 --> 00:28:08,656
The full troupe?

561
00:28:09,609 --> 00:28:10,297
Yes.

562
00:28:11,869 --> 00:28:12,738
Three days?

563
00:28:13,500 --> 00:28:14,092
Three full days?

564
00:28:15,090 --> 00:28:17,767
Yes, of course. We’d be very happy to.

565
00:28:19,148 --> 00:28:20,296
Yes.

566
00:28:20,296 --> 00:28:21,734
Alright, goodbye.

567
00:28:26,656 --> 00:28:28,756
No one needs to go on TV next week.

568
00:28:29,690 --> 00:28:31,356
Because we’ve got a job.

569
00:28:31,880 --> 00:28:34,292
Yay!

570
00:28:55,438 --> 00:28:57,972
♪ For I miss♪

571
00:28:58,925 --> 00:29:01,448
♪ I long for♪

572
00:29:03,823 --> 00:29:05,385
♪ Father dear,♪

573
00:29:06,099 --> 00:29:08,656
♪ Mother dear,♪

574
00:29:09,227 --> 00:29:11,172
♪ your child who stands here.♪

575
00:29:12,887 --> 00:29:15,929
♪ Every teaching♪

576
00:29:17,263 --> 00:29:19,684
♪ you once planted♪

577
00:29:20,875 --> 00:29:24,690
♪ deep within my heart.♪

578
00:29:26,500 --> 00:29:29,223
♪ I remember♪

579
00:29:31,271 --> 00:29:33,106
♪ those teachings♪

580
00:29:33,820 --> 00:29:36,002
♪ of Father and Mother,♪

581
00:29:38,390 --> 00:29:40,034
♪ the words you spoke,♪

582
00:29:41,796 --> 00:29:43,830
♪ this child of yours♪

583
00:29:44,618 --> 00:29:50,617
♪ has kept them in my heart.♪

584
00:29:58,956 --> 00:29:59,756
P’Phet.

585
00:30:00,856 --> 00:30:03,190
Why are you sitting out in the night air?

586
00:30:04,790 --> 00:30:06,156
You’ll get sick.

587
00:30:08,490 --> 00:30:09,756
The air feels nice and cool.

588
00:30:18,790 --> 00:30:20,140
It reminds me of when we were kids.

589
00:30:21,617 --> 00:30:23,492
After we finished Likay practice,

590
00:30:23,921 --> 00:30:25,444
we’d sit here together.

591
00:30:26,254 --> 00:30:27,396
You,

592
00:30:27,396 --> 00:30:28,863
Guy,

593
00:30:29,244 --> 00:30:30,799
and we’d sneak snacks.

594
00:30:31,823 --> 00:30:33,023
Then Father would scold us.

595
00:30:34,223 --> 00:30:35,456
Because we spilled the snacks.

596
00:30:35,856 --> 00:30:36,680
I remember.

597
00:30:37,061 --> 00:30:38,937
You got scolded the most.

598
00:30:40,195 --> 00:30:41,490
Because I’m the older one.

599
00:30:42,790 --> 00:30:43,942
My duty

600
00:30:44,561 --> 00:30:46,642
is to take care of everyone.

601
00:30:51,856 --> 00:30:53,556
I miss our mentors.

602
00:30:56,990 --> 00:30:58,359
Even though they’re gone,

603
00:30:59,169 --> 00:31:01,535
they left their knowledge for all of us.

604
00:31:03,678 --> 00:31:04,716
Next week’s show,

605
00:31:04,933 --> 00:31:07,627
I’ll give it everything.

606
00:31:08,437 --> 00:31:10,447
I’ll use everything I’ve learned

607
00:31:11,304 --> 00:31:13,280
to take care of everyone

608
00:31:14,856 --> 00:31:17,490
just like Master Mentor entrusted me to.

609
00:31:21,456 --> 00:31:22,542
And you

610
00:31:22,875 --> 00:31:24,493
shouldn’t keep looking after everyone else

611
00:31:25,303 --> 00:31:27,000
until you forget to take care of yourself.

612
00:31:27,714 --> 00:31:28,748
If you’re tired,

613
00:31:28,748 --> 00:31:30,675
you should rest.

614
00:31:32,247 --> 00:31:33,275
Or else

615
00:31:34,799 --> 00:31:36,635
let me take care of you sometimes.

616
00:31:39,255 --> 00:31:40,229
Because I—

617
00:31:50,456 --> 00:31:50,956
Ugh.

618
00:31:50,956 --> 00:31:52,235
I’m sleepy.

619
00:31:52,854 --> 00:31:54,191
I’m going to bed.

620
00:31:55,090 --> 00:31:56,312
Suddenly I’m sleepy.

621
00:31:59,756 --> 00:32:00,556
Hey.

622
00:32:01,590 --> 00:32:02,823
What are you doing here?

623
00:32:03,690 --> 00:32:04,823
Just dusting.

624
00:32:05,090 --> 00:32:05,590
Oops.

625
00:32:05,590 --> 00:32:07,320
There’s so much dust lately.

626
00:32:07,537 --> 00:32:09,015
It’s all messy—the window’s smeared.

627
00:32:10,790 --> 00:32:11,590
What are you doing?

628
00:32:11,591 --> 00:32:12,700
(Ping) The window’s dirty.
(Tor Prakai) Practicing dance.

629
00:32:14,456 --> 00:32:15,090
Oh man.

630
00:32:15,090 --> 00:32:16,469
Totally off.

631
00:32:18,756 --> 00:32:19,623
I’m going to bed.

632
00:32:23,790 --> 00:32:25,421
Good night, P’Phet.

633
00:32:25,421 --> 00:32:26,990
Good night.

634
00:32:27,490 --> 00:32:28,290
Good night.

635
00:32:28,356 --> 00:32:29,423
Good night.

636
00:32:30,256 --> 00:32:31,056
I’m heading off.

637
00:32:38,867 --> 00:32:41,459
♪ I’ll kill you.♪

638
00:32:41,697 --> 00:32:45,519
♪ You won’t live to see tomorrow.♪

639
00:32:45,852 --> 00:32:50,015
♪ Because you killed my father,♪

640
00:32:50,856 --> 00:32:53,049
♪ I’ve come to claim vengeance.♪

641
00:32:53,962 --> 00:32:54,934
You wicked thief!

642
00:32:55,195 --> 00:32:56,768
I will avenge my father!

643
00:32:57,101 --> 00:32:57,973
Come on.

644
00:33:32,311 --> 00:33:35,090
♪ My mission♪

645
00:33:35,423 --> 00:33:37,756
♪ is now fulfilled:♪

646
00:33:41,823 --> 00:33:45,490
♪ to avenge♪

647
00:33:47,538 --> 00:33:50,048
♪ my father.♪

648
00:34:04,756 --> 00:34:06,945
These past few days,
I really want to thank everyone.

649
00:34:07,612 --> 00:34:08,945
For giving it your all.

650
00:34:09,802 --> 00:34:10,941
As for tomorrow,

651
00:34:11,227 --> 00:34:13,109
I want everyone to give it everything.

652
00:34:13,190 --> 00:34:13,990
Give it everything,

653
00:34:14,890 --> 00:34:16,490
as if it were our last performance.

654
00:34:16,890 --> 00:34:17,690
Our last.

655
00:34:18,256 --> 00:34:20,023
Because if tomorrow’s show goes well,

656
00:34:20,356 --> 00:34:21,156
if we make it through,

657
00:34:22,156 --> 00:34:23,456
more jobs will follow.

658
00:34:23,856 --> 00:34:24,656
They will follow.

659
00:34:26,390 --> 00:34:27,490
Let’s fight together.

660
00:34:27,856 --> 00:34:29,156
Let’s fight together.

661
00:34:43,682 --> 00:34:45,438
Ew.

662
00:34:45,438 --> 00:34:46,019
Whoa.

663
00:34:46,019 --> 00:34:46,771
Was that a fart?

664
00:34:47,390 --> 00:34:48,780
I didn’t fart.

665
00:34:48,822 --> 00:34:50,000
(Ping) Rotten guts!
(Ploy Ying) That was loud!

666
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:51,543
(Chae) It was you!
(Pong) I said I didn’t fart.

667
00:34:52,209 --> 00:34:53,148
I can’t take it anymore.

668
00:34:53,687 --> 00:34:54,991
(Pleng Chai) Smell it all the way.
(Pong) I didn’t fart!

669
00:34:54,991 --> 00:34:55,839
You better smell all of it.

670
00:34:55,839 --> 00:34:56,604
Until it’s gone, okay?

671
00:34:57,453 --> 00:34:58,279
I said I didn’t fart.

672
00:35:00,556 --> 00:35:01,752
It’s not that bad.

673
00:35:07,499 --> 00:35:08,019
Well—

674
00:35:08,496 --> 00:35:09,847
Let’s go with this for everything.

675
00:35:10,000 --> 00:35:11,197
just do it like we practiced.

676
00:35:12,007 --> 00:35:13,281
Just give it your best.

677
00:35:13,390 --> 00:35:13,911
P’Phet.

678
00:35:14,435 --> 00:35:15,271
So—

679
00:35:15,985 --> 00:35:17,780
Do we know where the truck should go?

680
00:35:18,018 --> 00:35:18,922
Did they send you the location yet?

681
00:35:19,690 --> 00:35:20,490
Let me check.

682
00:35:24,290 --> 00:35:25,393
They haven’t sent it yet.

683
00:35:25,726 --> 00:35:27,989
Alright, I’ll call them.

684
00:35:38,356 --> 00:35:40,223
What? You can’t reach them?

685
00:35:41,556 --> 00:35:44,656
Isn’t this strange?

686
00:35:52,390 --> 00:35:54,856
Who’s our host today?

687
00:35:56,856 --> 00:35:58,290
Mae Boonruen Gold Shop.

688
00:36:02,190 --> 00:36:04,256
Then why did they post this on their page?

689
00:36:05,690 --> 00:36:06,490
What?

690
00:36:07,356 --> 00:36:08,499
Let me see.

691
00:36:08,499 --> 00:36:09,347
Mae Boonruen Gold Shop

692
00:36:09,347 --> 00:36:10,290
Featuring the beloved likay duo,
Jomtien and Jandao

693
00:36:10,290 --> 00:36:11,090
Hey.

694
00:36:11,456 --> 00:36:12,256
What is it?

695
00:36:21,256 --> 00:36:21,756
Wait—

696
00:36:22,042 --> 00:36:24,876
What about everything we prepared?

697
00:36:25,190 --> 00:36:25,990
Whoa.

698
00:36:27,790 --> 00:36:30,056
What do we do now?

699
00:36:31,823 --> 00:36:34,290
Didn’t we prepare all night long?

700
00:36:35,190 --> 00:36:36,023
What should we do?

701
00:36:36,190 --> 00:36:37,823
We prepared everything. What do we do?

702
00:36:39,490 --> 00:36:40,290
P’Phet.

703
00:36:41,456 --> 00:36:42,574
Did they ditch us?

704
00:36:42,574 --> 00:36:43,456
Looks like it.

705
00:36:45,223 --> 00:36:46,023
Hey.

706
00:36:46,490 --> 00:36:47,290
Everyone!

707
00:36:47,956 --> 00:36:49,356
Everyone, stay calm.

708
00:36:51,056 --> 00:36:52,712
(Pleng Chai) Stay calm
(Phet Tae) Calm down first.

709
00:36:53,147 --> 00:36:54,147
How can we stay calm?

710
00:36:54,246 --> 00:36:55,256
Calm down.

711
00:36:55,256 --> 00:36:56,690
We prepared everything.

712
00:36:57,623 --> 00:37:00,090
Exactly. We prepared everything.

713
00:37:01,223 --> 00:37:02,256
So we keep going.

714
00:37:02,690 --> 00:37:03,490
Keep going.

715
00:37:05,856 --> 00:37:07,492
If we don’t have a host,

716
00:37:08,159 --> 00:37:10,009
then we’ll host it ourselves.

717
00:37:10,485 --> 00:37:13,958
Ploy Ying and Tor Prakai, go get dressed.

718
00:37:13,958 --> 00:37:15,606
Wear the full costumes.

719
00:37:15,606 --> 00:37:18,101
Ping Pong Chae, set up the stage.

720
00:37:18,101 --> 00:37:19,000
Get everything ready.

721
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:21,625
We’ll set up the stage here at our house.

722
00:37:21,842 --> 00:37:22,807
What?

723
00:37:33,590 --> 00:37:35,417
Where will the audience be, P’Phet?

724
00:37:35,417 --> 00:37:37,056
Our house isn’t that big.

725
00:37:37,823 --> 00:37:39,168
Right here at our house.

726
00:37:39,168 --> 00:37:41,239
Thousands of viewers.

727
00:37:41,239 --> 00:37:42,987
If we can’t go to the audience,

728
00:37:43,552 --> 00:37:45,023
we’ll bring them to us.

729
00:37:45,023 --> 00:37:45,823
Yeah.

730
00:37:47,623 --> 00:37:50,375
Because we’ll livestream

731
00:37:50,375 --> 00:37:52,956
our Likay performance on social media for the first time.

732
00:37:53,484 --> 00:37:54,093
Today at 7:00 PM

733
00:37:54,093 --> 00:37:54,876
Watch the full performance by Phet Prakai Likay Troupe

734
00:37:54,877 --> 00:37:55,573
FREE!!! Live on this page

735
00:37:59,990 --> 00:38:00,823
Has the livestream started yet?

736
00:38:01,690 --> 00:38:02,356
Ready.

737
00:38:02,356 --> 00:38:03,290
Is the signal okay?

738
00:38:03,456 --> 00:38:04,256
Ready.

739
00:38:04,423 --> 00:38:06,356
Will it be worth what you invested?

740
00:38:06,856 --> 00:38:07,656
I don’t know.

741
00:38:08,490 --> 00:38:10,056
Whether it will be worth it or not.

742
00:38:10,656 --> 00:38:12,656
But it’s better than doing nothing.

743
00:38:13,223 --> 00:38:15,756
But if everyone gives it their all,

744
00:38:16,290 --> 00:38:17,856
the result will definitely be good.

745
00:38:25,356 --> 00:38:26,456
Everyone, attention.

746
00:38:26,717 --> 00:38:27,517
Let’s begin.

747
00:38:27,778 --> 00:38:28,850
Alright.

748
00:38:28,850 --> 00:38:29,784
(Pleng Chai) One, two.
(Phet Tae) Everyone’s confident, right?

749
00:38:29,784 --> 00:38:30,584
Three.

750
00:38:47,164 --> 00:38:47,860
The comments are coming in.

751
00:38:55,129 --> 00:38:56,376
♪ Allow me to present♪

752
00:38:56,975 --> 00:38:58,190
♪ the gallant hero,♪

753
00:38:59,074 --> 00:39:01,225
♪ handsome and radiant,♪

754
00:39:03,939 --> 00:39:05,707
♪ whose noble name♪

755
00:39:05,707 --> 00:39:11,374
♪ is Tor Prakai.♪

756
00:39:21,690 --> 00:39:22,490
I,

757
00:39:24,556 --> 00:39:27,290
—You won’t be famous this year. Maybe next live.

758
00:39:29,290 --> 00:39:30,856
am known as Tor Prakai,

759
00:39:31,356 --> 00:39:33,690
with three loyal warriors by my side.

760
00:39:34,856 --> 00:39:35,990
How fare you all?

761
00:39:37,090 --> 00:39:38,556
Your Highness, may I speak?

762
00:39:38,890 --> 00:39:40,790
Your servant wishes to share a grievance.

763
00:39:42,680 --> 00:39:43,889
Greetings, all ma’ams.

764
00:39:44,746 --> 00:39:46,854
The reason we started the live late today

765
00:39:47,855 --> 00:39:48,355
is because

766
00:39:49,214 --> 00:39:51,151
I had diarrhea.

767
00:39:51,956 --> 00:39:53,456
So I rushed to the restroom.

768
00:39:53,656 --> 00:39:55,223
There were three bathrooms.

769
00:39:55,423 --> 00:39:56,390
So I went to the first one.

770
00:39:57,023 --> 00:39:58,863
The first had water but no dipper.

771
00:39:58,863 --> 00:39:59,423
Hey!

772
00:40:00,156 --> 00:40:03,523
The second had a dipper but no water.

773
00:40:03,523 --> 00:40:04,023
Hey!

774
00:40:04,556 --> 00:40:07,190
I didn’t know what to do, so I went to the third.

775
00:40:08,956 --> 00:40:12,668
This one had everything, water and a dipper.

776
00:40:13,144 --> 00:40:14,966
But no door.

777
00:40:15,690 --> 00:40:16,623
So what did you do?

778
00:40:16,756 --> 00:40:17,556
Yeah, what did you do?

779
00:40:17,690 --> 00:40:19,210
So I closed my eyes and did it.

780
00:40:19,210 --> 00:40:19,890
Hey!

781
00:40:26,001 --> 00:40:27,305
Sorry

782
00:41:05,908 --> 00:41:07,522
♪ Hello.♪

783
00:41:08,665 --> 00:41:11,729
♪ Beautiful ma’ams.♪

784
00:41:15,380 --> 00:41:17,380
♪ Thank you♪

785
00:41:17,380 --> 00:41:23,238
♪ for all your support.♪

786
00:41:47,190 --> 00:41:48,944
Everyone did great, really great.

787
00:41:48,944 --> 00:41:50,396
Thank you so much.

788
00:41:50,396 --> 00:41:51,956
Thank you everyone. Today was amazing.

789
00:41:53,190 --> 00:41:53,990
We did it.

790
00:41:54,623 --> 00:41:55,423
How was it?

791
00:41:55,656 --> 00:41:56,330
Pleng.

792
00:41:56,330 --> 00:41:57,259
Our livestream audience

793
00:41:57,259 --> 00:41:57,856
Oh.

794
00:41:58,023 --> 00:41:59,056
I checked.

795
00:41:59,756 --> 00:42:01,023
Just the viewers

796
00:42:01,156 --> 00:42:02,790
have already passed three thousand.

797
00:42:03,956 --> 00:42:04,756
Three thousand.

798
00:42:05,823 --> 00:42:07,756
And the gifts sent

799
00:42:09,256 --> 00:42:10,056
forty thousand in total.

800
00:42:10,856 --> 00:42:11,656
Forty thousand.

801
00:42:12,023 --> 00:42:12,823
Forty thousand.

802
00:42:15,356 --> 00:42:16,190
Nice, nice.

803
00:42:16,856 --> 00:42:17,615
But I

804
00:42:18,006 --> 00:42:20,590
checked P’Jomthian and P’Jandao’s live earlier.

805
00:42:21,090 --> 00:42:22,409
Their live viewers…

806
00:42:22,670 --> 00:42:24,190
are already over five thousand.

807
00:42:24,623 --> 00:42:26,790
Wow, very popular.

808
00:42:26,890 --> 00:42:27,423
Hmm.

809
00:42:27,423 --> 00:42:29,490
I think it’s because they appeared on TV.

810
00:42:29,890 --> 00:42:31,390
Then should we go on TV too?

811
00:42:31,914 --> 00:42:32,928
What show would you go on?

812
00:42:33,166 --> 00:42:34,138
The show

813
00:42:34,138 --> 00:42:35,587
Thup Toh Khao.

814
00:42:36,254 --> 00:42:37,299
What show is that?

815
00:42:37,690 --> 00:42:38,353
Come on, come on.

816
00:42:38,745 --> 00:42:40,269
Go change clothes.

817
00:42:40,269 --> 00:42:41,008
Go, go.

818
00:42:41,008 --> 00:42:41,834
What show is that?

819
00:42:46,630 --> 00:42:47,321
Go, go.

820
00:42:47,321 --> 00:42:48,272
Change clothes.

821
00:42:56,167 --> 00:42:57,823
You were so beautiful.
I watched from start to finish.

822
00:43:06,062 --> 00:43:06,562
Thank you.

823
00:43:10,277 --> 00:43:11,272
My senior who is a director

824
00:43:11,272 --> 00:43:12,500
saw your photos and liked them.

825
00:43:12,500 --> 00:43:14,500
He wants you, P’Ploy Ying,
to audition for a series.

826
00:43:14,500 --> 00:43:16,500
Are you interested?

827
00:43:29,978 --> 00:43:31,026
Forty thousand.

828
00:43:41,156 --> 00:43:43,190
Oh, you’re not asleep yet?

829
00:43:48,256 --> 00:43:50,623
Aren’t you sleepy, Ploy?

830
00:43:50,990 --> 00:43:53,756
Not yet. My hair just dried.

831
00:43:53,756 --> 00:43:54,956
Come here. I’ll comb it for you.

832
00:43:56,223 --> 00:43:57,223
Be gentle.

833
00:44:02,456 --> 00:44:03,590
Were you tired today?

834
00:44:05,090 --> 00:44:08,590
A little, but it was more fun.

835
00:44:14,756 --> 00:44:15,623
All done.

836
00:44:19,856 --> 00:44:20,999
Thanks.

837
00:44:21,173 --> 00:44:23,190
I’m beautiful because of you.

838
00:44:25,256 --> 00:44:27,856
Consider it a reward for a talented heroine.

839
00:44:30,490 --> 00:44:31,331
P’Phet.

840
00:44:31,998 --> 00:44:35,123
If one day I get on TV,

841
00:44:35,423 --> 00:44:37,890
will more people know Petchprakai?

842
00:44:41,490 --> 00:44:42,890
Do you want to go?

843
00:44:46,456 --> 00:44:47,355
I don’t know.

844
00:44:47,927 --> 00:44:48,889
But

845
00:44:49,270 --> 00:44:51,641
besides being Petchprakai’s heroine,

846
00:44:52,213 --> 00:44:54,719
I don’t want to do anything else.

847
00:44:56,256 --> 00:44:59,990
But Petchprakai is struggling right now.

848
00:45:00,890 --> 00:45:02,273
So I

849
00:45:03,083 --> 00:45:04,343
want to help somehow.

850
00:45:07,056 --> 00:45:07,614
Ploy.

851
00:45:08,805 --> 00:45:10,012
I don’t want you

852
00:45:10,273 --> 00:45:12,328
forcing yourself.

853
00:45:13,281 --> 00:45:14,556
Don’t worry about Petchprakai.

854
00:45:15,856 --> 00:45:17,623
I’ll find a way.

855
00:45:24,490 --> 00:45:25,541
P’Phet.

856
00:45:25,874 --> 00:45:27,197
I told you already.

857
00:45:28,387 --> 00:45:30,137
That I want to repay you.

858
00:45:35,190 --> 00:45:36,056
I will go.

859
00:45:36,690 --> 00:45:37,990
And I will make it happen.

860
00:45:38,956 --> 00:45:41,090
And if one day I appear on TV,

861
00:45:42,156 --> 00:45:44,290
I will make the Petchprakai Likay Troupe

862
00:45:44,576 --> 00:45:47,142
famous across the country.

863
00:45:57,756 --> 00:45:58,556
Thank you.

864
00:46:01,790 --> 00:46:03,423
But first, pass the audition.

865
00:46:03,790 --> 00:46:04,445
Come on.

866
00:46:04,709 --> 00:46:06,036
P’Phet.

867
00:46:06,369 --> 00:46:09,406
This is Master Mentor’s top student.

868
00:46:11,956 --> 00:46:12,756
You’ll pass for sure.

869
00:46:13,590 --> 00:46:14,668
Fail.

870
00:46:14,859 --> 00:46:16,014
Pass.

871
00:46:35,590 --> 00:46:37,200
From this day on,

872
00:46:37,819 --> 00:46:40,509
may only good things come your way.

873
00:46:43,490 --> 00:46:45,156
Does a bar pay well?

874
00:46:45,456 --> 00:46:47,390
Boss, are you stealing my job?

875
00:46:47,556 --> 00:46:49,956
I’ve already thought of a name. Cheem Choei.

876
00:46:50,790 --> 00:46:51,590
Our place

877
00:46:52,190 --> 00:46:53,556
will be the hottest in the area.

878
00:47:00,023 --> 00:47:00,987
Hey, Guy.

879
00:47:01,938 --> 00:47:02,856
Breaking news.

880
00:47:03,223 --> 00:47:04,890
P’Ploy Ying is going to audition for a series.

881
00:47:05,190 --> 00:47:05,965
This Saturday.

882
00:47:05,965 --> 00:47:08,756
Something like I See You House.

883
00:47:09,223 --> 00:47:10,023
Really?

884
00:47:10,590 --> 00:47:11,390
Yes.

885
00:47:11,623 --> 00:47:12,423
No.

886
00:47:12,790 --> 00:47:13,490
Yes.

887
00:47:13,490 --> 00:47:14,256
No, it’s not.

888
00:47:14,256 --> 00:47:15,823
Something with I See You.

889
00:47:16,056 --> 00:47:16,890
An ambulance?

890
00:47:22,404 --> 00:47:24,674
Guy, the producer likes your photos.

891
00:47:24,674 --> 00:47:26,103
They want you to audition this Saturday.

892
00:47:26,103 --> 00:47:27,531
In the afternoon at I See You Studio.

893
00:47:31,756 --> 00:47:32,260
Hey.

894
00:47:32,260 --> 00:47:32,890
Shit.

895
00:47:35,823 --> 00:47:36,690
What should I do?

896
00:47:38,023 --> 00:47:39,656
What did you say earlier? I See You what?

897
00:47:39,956 --> 00:47:40,790
Is it the same one?

898
00:47:42,656 --> 00:47:43,656
What was it again? I See You?

899
00:47:45,990 --> 00:47:46,790
Exactly.

900
00:47:48,490 --> 00:47:50,023
I don’t know, man.

901
00:47:55,016 --> 00:47:55,799
Shit!

902
00:47:58,190 --> 00:47:59,423
It’s the same.

903
00:48:07,901 --> 00:48:10,604
♪ My wandering heart takes flight,♪

904
00:48:11,080 --> 00:48:13,077
♪ adrift in restless night,♪

905
00:48:14,823 --> 00:48:17,259
♪ I fear you’ll slip from sight,♪

906
00:48:17,259 --> 00:48:18,990
♪ and fade beyond my light.♪

907
00:48:20,623 --> 00:48:23,604
♪ Should you find love anew,♪

908
00:48:23,604 --> 00:48:26,256
♪ and never return in view,♪

909
00:48:27,690 --> 00:48:30,957
♪ our fragile love would fall,♪

910
00:48:32,005 --> 00:48:34,136
♪ and sorrow claim it all.♪

911
00:48:35,566 --> 00:48:38,538
♪ The thought alone brings tears,♪

912
00:48:39,205 --> 00:48:40,862
♪ and wakes my silent fears,♪

913
00:48:42,719 --> 00:48:46,075
♪ for none may stand against♪

914
00:48:46,647 --> 00:48:49,480
♪ the mighty will of fate.♪

915
00:49:20,256 --> 00:49:21,455
This time in Bangkok,

916
00:49:21,455 --> 00:49:23,098
I’m counting on you guys.

917
00:49:23,098 --> 00:49:25,188
I’ll go to the casting.

918
00:49:25,188 --> 00:49:26,534
You go find what

919
00:49:26,534 --> 00:49:27,690
P’Phet asked us to buy.

920
00:49:28,156 --> 00:49:29,336
Damn, P’Ploy.

921
00:49:29,336 --> 00:49:31,005
If she passes the audition,

922
00:49:31,005 --> 00:49:32,677
will she come back?

923
00:49:32,677 --> 00:49:33,823
Bangkok is really convenient.

924
00:49:34,390 --> 00:49:36,156
If you want the gear from me,

925
00:49:36,856 --> 00:49:37,856
how would you beg?

926
00:49:38,856 --> 00:49:39,656
Come on.

927
00:49:39,790 --> 00:49:41,090
Show me.

928
00:49:41,623 --> 00:49:43,556
And if I want to act in the series,

929
00:49:44,423 --> 00:49:46,223
you’ll let me do it, right?
